<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[188,1398,311,443]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
One of the female specimens from Orpen Gate of KNP shows a distinctly less downcurved and more elongate rostrum. This divergent phenotype exceeds the variability commonly observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[1246,1398,346,372]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1246,1398,346,372]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ebenacobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,295,382,408]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[379,513,381,407]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
in general and could indicate that several closely related species might exist in this species in its current concept.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[189,335,482,508]" box="[189,335,482,508]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,482,508]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,482,508]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Life history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[188,1399,529,626]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,550,529,555]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippopotamorum" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,550,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ebenacobius hippopotamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[559,737,529,555]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was collected on flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[1076,1284,529,555]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Euclea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[1076,1284,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Euclea natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is probably its host plant. This species was collected in sympatry with 
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[975,1136,565,590]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectirostris" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[975,1136,565,590]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">E. rectirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1142,1315,564,590]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
on this plant, although in smaller numbers. Adults were collected in July and October.
</paragraph>
